  "prompt": "Which is best 2 in 1 laptop under Rs 25000?",
  "response": "Finding a high-quality 2-in-1 laptop under Rs 25,000 can be challenging, as these devices typically come with more advanced hardware and features that can drive up the price. However, you might be able to find some budget-friendly options from lesser-known brands or during discounts and sales. Here are a few options that could fit within your budget:\n\n1. **Avita Cosmos 2-in-1 Laptop**:\n   - **Features**: 11.6-inch Full HD touchscreen, Intel Celeron N4000 processor, 4GB RAM, 64GB SSD, Windows 10 Home.\n   - **Pros**: Lightweight and portable, good display quality, and comes with a detachable keyboard.\n   - **Cons**: Limited storage and RAM, suitable for light tasks only.\n\n2. **RDP ThinBook 1110**:\n   - **Features**: 11.6-inch HD display, Intel Atom x5-Z8350 processor, 2GB RAM, 32GB SSD, Windows 10.\n   - **Pros**: Affordable, compact and lightweight, suitable for basic tasks like browsing and document editing.\n   - **Cons**: Limited performance, storage, and RAM, not ideal for multitasking.\n\n3. **Lenovo Ideapad Duet Chromebook**:\n   - **Features**: 10.1-inch FHD display, MediaTek Helio P60T processor, 4GB RAM, 64GB eMMC, Chrome OS.\n   - **Pros**: Great display, compact and portable, good battery life, comes with a keyboard and stand.\n   - **Cons**: Limited offline functionality due to Chrome OS, relatively small storage.\n\nKeep in mind that pricing and availability can change, so it's a good idea to check online retailers, read customer reviews, and possibly wait for sales or discounts to get the best deal. For the most part, these budget 2-in-1 laptops will be best suited for light usage such as web browsing, streaming, document editing, and basic applications. If you need more power for demanding tasks, you may need to increase your budget.",
